Residents of the northern Chilean
city of Calama staged protests today to pressure authorities for
increased funding,  Radio Bio-Bio  reported on its website.  At least one police officer was injured while seven people
were arrested, including city Mayor Esteban Velasquez, Bio-Bio
 reported . Calama is near the Chuquicamata copper mine, which is
